SIMPLE: waspish
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Waspish
<hw>Wasp"ish</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>Resembling a wasp in form; having a slender waist, like a
wasp.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Quick to resent a trifling affront; characterized by
snappishness; irritable; irascible; petulant; snappish.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>He was naturally a <qex>waspish</qex> and hot man.</q>
<rj><qau>Bp. Hall.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Much do I suffer, much, to keep in peace⟦br⟧
This jealous, <qex>waspish</qex>, wrong-head, rhyming race.</q>
<rj><qau>Pope.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Snappish; petulant; irritable; irascible; testy;
peevish; captious.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p>-- <wordforms><wf>Wasp"ish*ly</wf>, <pos>adv.</pos> --
<wf>Wasp"ish*ness</wf>, <pos>n.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Wassail</ent>⟦br⟧
